00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,800
I heard that you got married, but I'm not sure.
我听说你结婚了，但我不确定。

116
00:05:04,800 --> 00:05:07,120
So she's asking, did you get married?
所以她是在问：“你结婚了吗？”

117
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,920
If so, congratulations.
如果是的话，恭喜。

118
00:05:08,920 --> 00:05:09,920
That's right.
没错。

119
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:10,920
That's right.
没错。

120
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:15,420
So it's a very common way of starting a sentence when you are talking to someone and maybe
所以这是一个非常常见的句子开头方式，当你和某人说话时，也许

121
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:20,840
you want them to confirm this news or this gossip or this rumor is true or not.
你想让他们确认这个消息、八卦或谣言是否真实。

122
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:23,160
I heard you got a promotion.
我听说你升职了。

123
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,160
That's right.
没错。

124
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:25,160
Congratulations.
恭喜。

125
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:27,200
So that's the way that you use this phrase.
这就是使用这个短语的方式。

126
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:34,120
I heard you or well, if you're using another person, I heard that Tom got divorced.
我听说你，或者如果你提到另一个人，我听说汤姆离婚了。

127
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:36,400
I heard Susie had a baby.
我听说苏西生了个孩子。

128
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,400
That's right.
没错。

129
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:38,400
All right.
好的。

130
