You could say, where did you go on holiday?
你可以说，你去哪里度假了？

171
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:28,600
But maybe in America, we'd prefer to say, where did you go on vacation?
但在美国，我们可能更喜欢说，你去哪里度假了？

172
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:29,720
On vacation.
"On vacation"。

173
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:30,720
So both are correct.
所以两种说法都正确。

174
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:35,080
You can say, we got married while on holiday or we got married while on vacation.
你可以说，我们在度假时结婚，或者我们在度假时结婚。

175
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,080
Both are correct.
两种都正确。

176
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:40,400
It's just a little bit of difference between British English and American English.
这只是英式英语和美式英语之间的一点小差异。

177
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:44,480
And then moving on, she said, well, they also wanted to get married, Michelle did, but they
然后继续，她说，嗯，他们也想要结婚，米歇尔也是，但他们不得不推迟婚礼。

178
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:47,200
had to postpone their wedding.
推迟他们的婚礼。

179
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,200
Okay.
好的。

180
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:52,160
To postpone something means to wait until later to do it.
"To postpone something" 意思是等到以后再去做。

181
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:56,680
So you maybe want to do it today, but it's raining today.
所以你可能今天想做，但今天下雨。

182
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:59,520
So you have to postpone until next week.
所以你不得不推迟到下周。

183
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:00,520
That's right.
没错。

184
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:02,480
So it's kind of like you had to delay, you had to wait.
所以这有点像你不得不延迟，不得不等待。

185
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,480
Yeah, that's right.
是的，没错。

186
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:10,880
So you could say that because of bad weather, the picnic will be postponed until next month.
所以你可以说，因为天气不好，野餐将推迟到下个月。

187
00:08:10,880 --> 00:08:11,880
Okay.
好的。

188
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:13,280
So that's the way they use postpone.
所以他们就是这样使用"postpone"的。

189
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:17,440
Now it's interesting because you have a P in between there, so it's postpone.
现在有趣的是，中间有一个P，所以是"postpone"。

190
00:08:17,440 --> 00:08:18,440
Postpone.
"Postpone"。

191
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:21,080
Yeah, it's an interesting word to pronounce.
是的，这是一个发音有趣的词。

192
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,080
Okay.
好的。

193
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:24,880
And well, they also had to postpone it because of money.
嗯，他们也因为钱的问题不得不推迟。

194
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:27,040
It's just very expensive.
只是太贵了。

195
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:31,400
And Melissa agrees by saying, I know what you mean.
梅丽莎同意说，我明白你的意思。

196
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:33,040
I know what you mean.
我明白你的意思。

197
00:08:33,040 --> 00:08:37,600
Now this is a really common phrase and this is something you'll hear with more relaxed
这是一个非常常见的短语，你会听到它在朋友之间更轻松的对话中出现。

198
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,600
conversations between friends.
它意味着我理解情况，或者我有同感。

199
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:45,000
It means I understand the situation or I feel the same way.
所以在这种情况下，我们只是没有钱。

200
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:47,000
So in this case, we just don't have the money.
梅丽莎在说，我明白你的意思。

201
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:49,280
Melissa's saying, I know what you mean.
它意味着我也在钱上遇到困难。

202
00:08:49,280 --> 00:08:52,720
It means I'm having a hard time with money too.
我也没有多少钱。

203
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:54,400
I don't have much money either.
没错。

204
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,400
That's right.
所以你理解她在说什么。

205
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:59,160
So you understand what she's talking about.
你也同意。

206
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:00,520
You also agree.
我明白你的意思。

207
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:02,120
I know what you mean.
这只是一种同意别人的方式。

208
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:04,160
It's just a way of agreeing with someone.
好的。

209
00:09:04,160 --> 00:09:05,160
All right.
然后她继续确认米歇尔说的话，说，我觉得上海越来越贵了。

210
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:12,400
And then she goes on to confirm what Michelle is saying by saying, I think Shanghai is getting
好的。

211
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:14,440
more and more expensive.
这是一个非常关键的句子结构。

212
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,440
All right.
我们有"more and more"，"more and more"。

213
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:18,960
Now this is a really, really key sentence structure here.
然后后面跟一个形容词。

214
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:22,240
We have more and more, more and more.
所以结构是"more and more"加形容词。

215
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:24,000
And then after that we have an adjective.
所以"more and more spicy"，"more and more funny"，"more and more expensive"。

216
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:27,600
So the structure is more and more adjectives.
所以在这种情况下，这个城市比以前更贵了。

217
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:34,960
So more and more spicy, more and more funny, more and more expensive.
没错。

218
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:40,440
So in this case, the city is more expensive than it was before.
而且它还在变得更贵。

219
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:41,440
That's right.
没错。

220
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,800
And it's still getting more expensive.
当你使用这个结构时，主要意思是当你说"more and more"，然后加上一个形容词，比如"expensive"或"beautiful"，它意味着它持续增长。

221
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:43,800
That's right.
它持续变得更贵、更美或更难。

222
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:48,220
That's the main idea when you use this structure is that when you say more and more and then
但记住，我们在这里使用的形容词是当你使用比较级时，你不能说，例如，你不能用"funny"。

223
00:09:48,220 --> 00:09:54,240
you add an adjective such as expensive or beautiful, it means that it continues to grow.
你不能说"you are getting more and more funny"，因为显然"funny"的比较级是"funnier"。

224
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:59,800
It continues to get more expensive or more beautiful or more difficult.
所以小心这一点，因为它可能有点让人困惑。

225
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:04,560
But remember that we are using adjectives here that are when you're using the comparative,
好的。

226
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:07,040
you can't say, for example, you can't use funny.
所以为了结束我们的流利度构建，我们有米歇尔同意梅丽莎，说，是的，你知道，我觉得上海越来越贵了。

227
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:10,640
You can't say you are getting more and more funny because obviously the comparative for
她说，"I sure do"。

228
00:10:10,640 --> 00:10:11,920
funny is funnier.
所以她基本上是在同意。

229
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:16,520
So just be careful with that one because it could be a little bit confusing.
她在说，是的，那是真的。

230
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:17,520
All right.
但为什么？

231
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:23,240
So and to finish off our fluency builder, we have Michelle who agrees with Melissa and
为什么她说"I sure do"？

232
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:27,280
says, yeah, you know, I think Shanghai is getting more expensive.
为什么她不说"agree"？

233
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:29,900
And she says, I sure do.
"I agree"或"yeah, you're right"。

234
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:30,900
So she's basically agreeing.
嗯，她不必说，因为她说了"I do"。

235
00:10:30,900 --> 00:10:33,320
She's saying, yes, that's true.
所以"do"在这里代替了"agree"。

236
00:10:33,320 --> 00:10:34,440
But why?
所以"do"是一个替代动词。

237
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,960
Why does she say I sure do?
所以她说"I sure do"意思是"我确实同意"。

238
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,840
Why doesn't she say agree?
所以这是一种非常常见的同意方式。

239
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:39,640
I agree or yeah, you're right.
是的，没错。

240
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:44,280
Well, she doesn't have to say it because she says I do.
所以"do"可以代替许多动词。

241
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:47,520
The question before that was, I think something, something, don't you?
之前那个问题是，我觉得是，什么什么，对吧？

242
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:49,040
And she says, I do.
然后她说，我愿意。

243
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:50,040
And I think that.
我也这么觉得。

244
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:52,920
So it's assumed that she also thinks this.
所以可以认为她也这么想。

245
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:54,160
She's answering a question.
她在回答一个问题。

246
00:10:54,160 --> 00:10:55,160
That's right.
没错。

247
00:10:55,160 --> 00:11:01,880
So that's an interesting way of asking a question when you say, I think the city is beautiful.
所以当你问“我觉得这个城市很美”时，这是一种有趣的提问方式。

248
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:02,880
Don't you?
对吧？

249
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:07,840
So the proper way to answer that would be I do or I sure do.
所以正确的回答应该是“我愿意”或“我当然愿意”。

250
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:08,840
All right.
好了。

251
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:10,680
So that's all the time we have for fluency builder.
这就是我们流利度训练的全部时间了。

252
00:11:10,680 --> 00:11:15,880
Let's listen to our dialogue one last time.
让我们最后听一遍对话。

253
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:27,400
Hey, Michelle, jumping quick.
嘿，Michelle，快跳进来。

254
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,400
It's pouring out there.
外面下着倾盆大雨。

255
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:32,080
Oh, hi, Melissa.
哦，嗨，Melissa。

256
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:33,880
Are you going to the conference too?
你也要去参加会议吗？

257
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:35,600
I was planning to pick up Mr. Campbell.
我本来打算去接Campbell先生。

258
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:40,200
Yes, he told me we need to pick him up at his hotel and then go to the conference.
是的，他告诉我我们需要去他酒店接他，然后去参加会议。

259
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,560
Oh, I see.
哦，我明白了。

260
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:44,120
OK, so I heard you got married.
好的，我听说你结婚了。

261
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,120
Congratulations.
恭喜。

262
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:46,400
Oh, thank you.
哦，谢谢。

263
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:48,000
I'm very excited.
我非常兴奋。

264
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:52,520
We were going to get married next year, but then we decided to get married on holiday
我们本来打算明年结婚，但后来决定在假期结婚

265
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:53,520
instead.
反而。

266
00:11:53,520 --> 00:11:54,520
It was wonderful.
那真是太棒了。

267
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:56,560
That sounds so romantic.
听起来真浪漫。

268
00:11:56,560 --> 00:12:02,120
Jack and I were hoping to get married in Europe next year, but we had to postpone our plans.
Jack和我本来希望明年在欧洲结婚，但我们不得不推迟计划。

269
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,620
We just don't have the money.
我们就是没钱。

270
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:05,000
I know what you mean.
我懂你的意思。

271
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:08,240
I think Shanghai is getting more and more expensive.
我觉得上海越来越贵了。

272
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,240
Don't you?
对吧？

273
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:10,240
I sure do.
我当然觉得。

274
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:13,880
In my opinion, it's actually becoming more expensive than back home.
在我看来，它实际上变得比家乡还贵。

275
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:14,880
Definitely.
绝对是。

276
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,240
Oh, there's Mr. Campbell.
哦，Campbell先生来了。

277
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:19,000
Driver, can you stop here, please?
司机，能在这儿停一下吗？

278
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:24,960
All right, so we're reaching the end of our small talk series.
好了，我们即将结束闲聊系列。

279
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:28,560
In this case, it's two women who are talking about their personal lives.
在这个案例中，是两个女人在谈论她们的私人生活。

280
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:32,400
And not only that, they're talking about weddings and they're talking about money.
不仅如此，她们还在谈论婚礼和钱。

281
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:38,960
So this is a very interesting way to talk about these very common topics, personal life,
所以这是一种非常有趣的方式来谈论这些非常常见的话题：私人生活、

282
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:41,000
love and especially money.
爱情，尤其是钱。

283
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:44,360
But remember, in American culture, these are the kinds of things you would only talk to
但记住，在美国文化中，这些是你只会和

284
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:45,360
your friends about.
朋友谈论的事情。

285
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:50,280
You wouldn't really want to talk to strangers about money, personal life, marriage, because
你不会真的想和陌生人谈论钱、私人生活、婚姻，因为

286
00:12:50,280 --> 00:12:51,720
those are considered private.
这些被认为是私密的。

287
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:54,880
So be careful when you're talking to people you don't know very well.
所以当你和不太熟悉的人交谈时要小心。

288
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:55,880
That's right.
没错。

289
00:12:55,880 --> 00:13:02,240
And actually, your feedback was very interesting when we discussed about if it's okay to ask,
实际上，当我们讨论是否适合问，比如，一个女人的年龄或体重或一个男人的薪水时，你的反馈非常有趣。

290
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:07,760
for example, a woman her age or her weight or a man's salary.
在大多数地方，你说这不太合适。

291
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:11,280
So in most places, you said that it wasn't really correct.
但这是关于文化差异和什么适合

292
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:17,560
But this is the very interesting thing about the cultural differences and what is appropriate
谈论的非常有趣的一点。

293
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:18,560
to talk about.
没错。

294
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,560
That's right.
所以再次强调，如果你对我们今天讨论的内容或我们关于闲聊的旧课程有任何问题或评论，

295
00:13:19,560 --> 00:13:22,840
So again, if you have any questions or comments about the things we talked about here today
请告诉我们。

296
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:27,880
or any of our older lessons about small talk, please just let us know.
我们的网站是EnglishPod.com。

297
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:28,880
Our website is EnglishPod.com.
好了，各位。

298
00:13:28,880 --> 00:13:29,880
All right, guys.
我们那儿见。

299
00:13:29,880 --> 00:13:30,880
We'll see you there.
感谢收看Polish English。

300
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:47,540
And thanks for watching Polish English.
好了。
